    "order": 4
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_2",
    "text": "pork belly bao buns and tacos, miso eggplant, and grilled steak with chimi- churri sauce. Chef Jesus Preciado's menu draws from Asia and Latin Amer- ica (including his native Colombia). On the cocktail list, find drinks like Beet the Heat (made with spicy pisco and beet syrup) and Amarillo Passion (in which tequila meets yuzu liqueur, passion fruit syrup, and the aji amarillo chile).",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.01392369813422445,
      0.07339167818209734,
      0.19883040935672514,
      0.14309841854752034
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 5
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_28",
    "text": "Soul on Shawmut",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.8025619604566973,
      0.0740058344848764,
      0.884990253411306,
      0.08014739751266697
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 6
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_29",
    "text": "Roxbury-raised chef Aadam Abdul- Musawwir began serving prepared meals and pop-up dinners as Aadam's Halal Meals. Now, he and two siblings have opened Soul on Shawmut to feed their community. Lightly updated soul food classics are on the menu, along with Buffalo chicken egg rolls, grilled cheese burgers, and more. Fried chick- en with Old Bay honey, smoked mac and cheese, slow-cooked collard greens with sauteed cabbage, sweet potato cheesecake, and hibiscus watermelon juice sounds pretty unbeatable for din- ner tonight.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8025619604566973,
      0.08106863196683556,
      0.98635477582846,
      0.18486104713649623
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 7
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_3",
    "text": "647 Tremont St., South End, Boston, 617-286-2333, www.desnudacoci- na.com. Smaller plates $6-$18, larger plates $18-$32, cocktails $14-$17.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.01392369813422445,
      0.1437125748502994,
      0.19827346143135616,
      0.17165668662674652
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 8
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_4",
    "text": "Kaia",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.013366750208855471,
      0.17871948410870567,
      0.03564466722361459,
      0.1845539689851067
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 9
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_5",
    "text": "The latest from Xenia Greek Hospi- tality, which brought us Bar Vlaha, Kra- si, and more. This time, culinary direc- tor Brendan Pelley and team whisk din- ers to the Aegean (with a South End mind-set) via dishes like sea bream cru- do with fermented squash broth; barley toasts with beets, pears, and vegan feta; black truffle spanakopita; and grilled whole fish. The wine list is devoted sole- ly to selections from the Aegean and Eastern Mediterranean islands.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.013366750208855471,
      0.18516812528788576,
      0.19827346143135616,
      0.26869338246583757
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 10
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_30",
    "text": "722A Sharemut Ave., Roxbury, 617- 238-7525, www.soulonshawmut.com. Sandwiches $10-$18, fried chicken $7-$18, sides $5, desserts $3-$6.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8025619604566973,
      0.18578228159066482,
      0.986911723753829,
      0.21372639336711194
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 11
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_31",
    "text": "Standard Italian",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.8025619604566973,
      0.22048211269768156,
      0.8794207741576162,
      0.22662367572547212
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 12
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_32",
    "text": "Where others fail, there is Italian food. Standard Italian, in the Eastern Standard complex looming over Fen- way, replaces the former All That Fish + Oyster, and it's a smart move. Lasagna bolognese, porchetta, and espresso martinis could just get us all through the winter. Culinary director Brian Rae is in his element, having previously worked at Coppa, Faccia a Faccia, and Rialto.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8025619604566973,
      0.22785198833103024,
      0.98635477582846,
      0.30370029172424384
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 13
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_6",
    "text": "370 Harrison Ave., South End, Bos- ton, 617-514-0700, ww.kaias0uth- end.com. Dishes $16-$44.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.01392369813422445,
      0.26930753876861663,
      0.1971595655806182,
      0.29018885306310455
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 14
  },
  {
