    "order": 16
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_12",
    "text": "Desnuda Cocina & Bar (above) and Russ & Mimi's (right) are among the many exciting restaurants arriving on the scene.",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.21052631578947367,
      0.289881774911715,
      0.3887496519075466,
      0.3184400429909412
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 17
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_7",
    "text": "Masons Steakhouse",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.013366750208855471,
      0.29786580684784275,
      0.10916179337231968,
      0.30370029172424384
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 18
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_33",
    "text": "771 Beacon St., Fenreay, Boston, 857- 305-3095, wrew.standarditalian.com. Appetizers $5-$20, entrees $28-$42, des- serts $9-$12.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8025619604566973,
      0.3043144480270229,
      0.98635477582846,
      0.33225855980346997
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 19
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_8",
    "text": "Here's what happens when a group of powerhouse South Shore culinary pros (including Jimmy Liang of JP Fuji Group and Kevin Long of Tosca) join forces. This swank Quincy steakhouse is located in a former Masonic temple and serves up lobster bisque, oysters Rocke- feller, pappardelle bolognese, salmon with spiced cauliflower — and, of course, beautiful steaks. The also-beau- tiful, creative desserts are from pastry chef and Masons co-owner Robert Gon- zalez, who is behind Quincy's Niveaux Patisserie. In a landscape (increasingly) stocked with steakhouses, it is nice to see a new one open with local owner- ship.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.013366750208855471,
      0.3052356824811915,
      0.19883040935672514,
      0.4225395363119914
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 20
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_13",
    "text": "Butcher Shop, smoky seafood chowder with Irish soda bread, shepherd's pie, bangers and mash, and other pub favor- ites are here, along with wood-fired piz- za, brunch (yes, full Irish breakfast), and festive cocktails. Or just drop in for live music and a proper pint of Guin- ness.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.21052631578947367,
      0.33195148165208044,
      0.3948760790866054,
      0.3878397052049747
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 21
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_34",
    "text": "Zurito",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.8025619604566973,
      0.33962843543681864,
      0.833194096351991,
      0.34546292031321973
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 22
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_35",
    "text": "It's named for the small glass of beer that often accompanies pintxos, the Basque take on tapas, and this Beacon Hill restaurant serves up plenty: Gildas, skewers of anchovies, peppers, and ol- ives; griddled shrimp with garlic and chile oil; mini croissants stuffed with ja- mon iberico; squid ink risotto. Cocktails such as the sherry-based Perfect Bam- boo and fizzy glasses of tzakolina are perfect accompaniments. Zurito, locat- ed in the longtime Bin 26 space, is run by chef Jamie Bissonnette, Babak Bina, and Andy Cartin of BCB3 Hospitality, al- so behind Somaek, Temple Records, and Sushi @ Temple Records.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.8025619604566973,
      0.3463841547673883,
      0.98635477582846,
      0.45754644557039764
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 23
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_14",
    "text": "367 Neponset Ave., Dorchester, 617- 514-4689, wrrw.mcgonagles.com. Appe- tizers $8-$16, pizza $18-$19, entrees $18-$34.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.21108326371484265,
      0.38845386150775374,
      0.3948760790866054,
      0.41578381698142175
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 24
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_17",
    "text": "JONATHAN WIGGS/GLOBE STAFF",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6633249791144528,
      0.42069706740365426,
      0.7875243664717348,
      0.42622447412866576
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 25
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_9",
    "text": "1170 Hancock St., Quincy, 617-689- 8818, wwre.masonssteakhouse.com. Ap- petizers $14-$32, entrees $29-$45, steaks $52-$160, sides $6-$14, desserts $12-$19.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.013366750208855471,
      0.4231536926147705,
      0.19771651350598718,
      0.4584676800245662
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 26
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_19",
    "text": "Mikiya Wagyu Shabu House",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.21164021164021163,
      0.42376784891754954,
      0.3419660261765525,
      0.43021649009672963
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 27
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_21",
    "text": "If you're starving, cold, and enjoy wagyu beef, Mikiya is calling you. This Chinatown restaurant serves all-you- can-eat wagyu hot pot at a variety of price points; you have 90 minutes to cook a variety of cuts in the broths of your choosing, while eating specialty dishes such as sweet shrimp sashimi and wagyu bone marrow, plus fruit and ice cream for dessert. Mikiya is a project from Chubby Group, whose Kevin Liu is also behind Matsunori Handroll Bar.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.21108326371484265,
      0.4311377245508982,
      0.3948760790866054,
      0.5140488254260709
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 28
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_25",
    "text": "",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.6048454469507101,
      0.4366651312759097,
      0.7897521581732108,
      0.49961615231076306
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033",
    "order": 29
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_22",
    "text": "Wagyu sets $45-$98 (less with annu- al membership; free or half-price for kids).",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.4071289334447229,
      0.43697220942729925,
      0.5914786967418546,
      0.4581606018731767
    ],
