  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_66",
    "text": "Stylish, swanky, and with a stellar chef attached (Jody Ad- ams), this Italian destination in- side Raffles Boston is the ulti- mate in special-occasion dining: The silken tagliatelle alone is worth the trip up that grand staircase. Sure, there's also an ex- tensive martini menu, but spirit- free drinks also get proper due. A nonalcoholic tangerine marga- rita with spirit-free tequila and lime is worth toasting. Not quite ready to abstain? There's also an extensive low-ABV list featuring treats like a Lambrusco Cobbler, made with black currant and berries. Good for: a celebratory splurge. 38 Trinity Place, Boston, 617-221-4200",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
