  {
    "chunk_id": "mineru_newspaper_TheBostonGlobe-2025-1-8@magazinesclubnew_page_033_61",
    "text": "This South Boston red-sauce lair might seem like the type of spot to throw back icy martinis (they do host Sinatra Sundays, af- ter all) paired with big plates of rigatoni Bolognese, but they also have warming $9 mocktails, like the Far From the Tree, with toasty apple cider, cardamom, allspice, thyme, and egg whites. In addition to catering to non- drinkers, they accommodate a range of palates, with gluten-free pasta on request. Good for: a night out with a group. 443 West Broadway, Boston, 617-993-8080",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
